&lt;h1&gt;Mersey Care NHS Trust&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Base: Secure Services&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Post: Nurse Team Leader Primary Health Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary: Band 6&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1 post – Permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A newly developed post has arisen to manage the Health Centre at Ashworth Hospital which will provide the opportunity to combine skills in Primary Health and High Secure care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Nurse Team Leader you will play a key role within the Health Centre, supporting the operational management on a day to day basis and the clinical agenda. The post holder will coordinate the daily activity within the Health Centre, demonstrating clinical skills in triage and ensuring high standards of compliance with security, Health and safety, quality and National targets. The post holder will have skills to assess diagnose and treat patients with a variety of illnesses, injuries and ailments under the guidance of the Nurse Practitioner and general Practitioners and will form part of the management structure for the junior team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The work will include close collaboration with a variety of internal and external professionals so effective communication is essential. Proven experience of managing a staffed area is essential in addition to having substantial clinical nursing experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mersey Care is committed to achieving a service that represents and reflects the diversity of service users and carers and the community it serves. We welcome applicants from under represented groups and communities such as Black Multi Ethnic, people with disabilities and lesbian, gay and bisexual communities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in attending for an informal visit or would like any further information about this opportunity contact Dale Williams, Modern Matron 0151 473 2851&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Short Listing 16th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews: 26th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDale WilliamsJob titleHead of Physical Health CareEmail addressdale.williams@merseycare.nhs.ukTelephone number0151 472 4567&lt;/p&gt;
